name: Catchpoint
description: Provides Dashabords as a central location for the Catchpoint tests in your account. View at-a-glance information surrounding your recent Errors. The Node Map provides a geographical overview of your test runs, while the Tests widget lets you search for and quickly access your synthetic data.

children.name: Catchpoint - Overview
children.description: The Overview dashboard is your central location for the Catchpoint tests in your account. View at-a-glance information surrounding your recent Errors and the Tests widget lets you search for and quickly access your synthetic data.
children.title: Catchpoint - Overview

queries.queryString:
$$logsrc  
| json field=_raw "Summary.Error.Code" as Errors
| if(Errors matches "50010", 1,0) as DNS_Errors
| sum(DNS_Errors) as DNS_Errors
$$logsrc  | json field=_raw "Summary.Error.Code" as Errors | if(Errors matches "50010", 1,0) as Errors_Count | timeslice 1m |sum(Errors_Count) as DNS_Errors by _timeslice
$$logsrc | json field=_raw "Summary.Error.Code" as Errors   |  if(Errors matches "50011", 1,0) as Errors_Count |  timeslice 1m | sum(Errors_Count) as Connection_Errors by _timeslice
$$logsrc  | json field=_raw "Summary.Error.Code" as Errors |  if(Errors matches "12175", 1,0) as Errors_Count | timeslice 1m | sum(Errors_Count) as SSL_Errors by _timeslice
$$logsrc  | json field=_raw "Summary.Error.Code" as Errors |  if(Errors matches "50005", 1,0) as Errors_Count | timeslice 1m | sum(Errors_Count) as Timeout_Errors by _timeslice
$$logsrc  | json field=_raw "Summary.Error.Code" as Errors |  if(Errors matches "50112", 1,0) as Errors_Count | timeslice 1m | sum(Errors_Count) as Transaction_Errors by _timeslice

$$logsrc  | json field=_raw "Summary.Error.Code" as Errors   |  if(Errors matches /^((?!((50010.*)|(50011.*)|(12175.*)|(50005.*)|(50112.*))).)*$/, 1,0) as Errors_Count | timeslice 1m |sum(Errors_Count) as Other_Errors by _timeslice

$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary","Summary.Error.Code","TestDetail.Name","TestId","Summary.Timing.Total" as Test_Runs,Errors,Test_Name,Test_Id,Test_Time nodrop
| if(Errors matches /\d*/,1,0) as Error_count | if(!isNull(Test_Runs),1,0) as Test_Runs
| avg(Test_Time) as Test_Time, sum(Error_count) as Error_count, sum(Test_Runs) as Test_Runs by Test_Name,Test_Id
| (Error_count/Test_Runs)*100 as Percent_Downtime | round (Percent_Downtime, 2) as Percent_Downtime
| round (Test_Time,2) as Test_Time 
| now() as Start_Timestamp
| Start_Timestamp - 3600000 as End_Timestamp
| tolong(Start_Timestamp) as Start_Timestamp
| tolong(End_Timestamp) as End_Timestamp
| formatDate(End_Timestamp, "MMddYYYYHHmm","America/New_York") as Start_Date
| formatDate(Start_Timestamp, "MMddYYYYHHmm","America/New_York") as End_Date
| concat ("https://portal.catchpoint.com/ui/Preview/Smartboard/Syn/?cs=1&testId=",Test_Id,"&time=",Start_Date,"_",End_Date,"_7_0_999") as TestUrl
| tourl (TestUrl,Test_Name) as Test_Name 
| compare with timeshift 3h 
| fields  Test_Name,Test_Time,Test_Time_3h,Percent_Downtime,Percent_Downtime_3h
| sort by Percent_Downtime
| limit 20

$$logsrc 
| _sourcehost as ip_address
| json field=_raw "Summary.Error.Code" as Errors
| if(Errors matches /\d*/,1,0) as Error_Count
| count  ip_address
| lookup latitude, longitude, country_code, country_name, region, city, postal_code from geo://location on ip = ip_address

$$logsrc  
| json field=_raw "Summary.Error.Code" as Errors 
| if(Errors matches /\d*/,1,0) as Error_Count 
| sum(Error_Count) as Error_Count

$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary.Timing.{{MetricNames}}","NodeName","TestId","TestDetail.Name" as {{MetricNames}},Node_Name,Test_Id,Test_Name
| timeslice 1m
| where Test_Name matches /^{{TestName}}$/ and Node_name matches /^{{NodeName}}$/
| avg ({{MetricNames}}) as {{MetricNames}}  by Node_Name,Test_Id,_timeslice
| transpose row _timeslice column  Node_Name,Test_Id

$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary.Error.Code" as Errors
| if(Errors matches "50011", 1,0) as Connection_Errors
| if(Errors matches "50005", 1,0) as Timeout_errors
| sum(Connection_Errors) as Connection_Errors

$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary.Error.Code" as Errors
| if(Errors matches "50005", 1,0) as Timeout_errors
| sum(Timeout_errors) as Timeout_errors

$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary.Error.Code" as Errors
| if(Errors matches "12175", 1,0) as SSL_errors
| sum(SSL_errors) as SSL_errors

$$logsrc  | json field=_raw "Summary.Error.Code" as Errors   | if(Errors matches "50010", 1,0) as DNS_Errors | if(Errors matches "50011", 1,0) as Connection_Errors | if(Errors matches /^((?!((50010.*)|(50011.*)|(50005.*)|(12175.*)|(50112.*))).)*$/, 1,0) as Other_errors | sum(Other_errors) as Other_errors
$$logsrc  | json field=_raw "Summary.Error.Code" as Errors   | if(Errors matches "50112", 1,0) as Transaction_Errors | sum(Transaction_Errors) as Transaction_Errors

$$logsrc 
| _sourcehost as ip_address
| count by ip_address 
| lookup latitude, longitude, country_code, country_name, region, city, postal_code from geo://location on ip = ip_address

children.name: Catchpoint - Recent Errors
children.description: The Errors page lists all the errors encountered by synthetic tests. This page makes it easy to view the top issues as well as narrow down on problems to identify commonality between failures for any given test or group of tests.
children.title: Catchpoint - Recent Errors

queries.queryString:
$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary","Summary.Error.Code","Summary.Timing.Total","NodeName","TestDetail.Name","TestId" as Test_runs,Error_Code,Total,Node_Name,Test_Name,TestId nodrop
| if(Error_Code matches "50010", "DNS_Errors",if(Error_Code matches "50005", "Timeout_errors",if(Error_Code matches "12175","SSL_Errors",if(Error_Code matches "50112", "Transaction_Errors",if(Error_Code matches /^((?!((50010.*)|(50011.*)|(50005.*) | (50112.*)|(12175.*))).)*$/,"Other_Errors","No_Errors"))))) as Error_Type
| where Error_Type != "No_Errors" and Test_Name matches /^.*$/
| timeslice 1m
| avg(Total) as Test_Time by Test_Name,_timeslice,Error_Code,Error_Type,Node_Name,TestId
| now() as Start_Timestamp
| tolong(Start_Timestamp) as Start_Timestamp
| formatDate(_timeslice, "MMddYYYHHmm","America/New_York") as Start_Date
| concat ("https://portal.catchpoint.com/ui/Preview/Record/Synthetic?t=",TestId,"&z=0&n=11&i=",Start_Date,"&v=0") as TestUrl
| tourl (TestUrl,Error_Type) as Error_Type  
| sort _timeslice 
| fields Test_Name,_timeslice,Error_Code,Error_Type,Node_Name,Test_Time

children.name: Catchpoint - Response Size
children.description: The Response size dashboard plots the amount of data downloaded when loading each resource. This highlights the amount of content and the headers download size over time.
children.title: Catchpoint - Response Size

queries.queryString:
$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary.Byte.Response.TotalContent","NodeName","TestId","TestDetail.Name" as TotalContent,Node_Name,Test_Id,Test_Name
| where Test_Name matches /^{{TestName}}$/
|  timeslice 1m 
| avg (TotalContent) as TotalContent  by Node_Name,Test_Id,_timeslice 
| TotalContent/1024/1024 as  TotalContent
| transpose row _timeslice column  Node_Name,Test_Id

$$logsrc  
| json field=_raw "Summary.Byte.Response.TotalHeaders","NodeName","TestId","TestDetail.Name" as TotalHeaders,Node_Name,Test_Id,Test_Name
| timeslice 1m
| where Test_Name matches /^{{TestName}}$/
| avg (TotalHeaders) as TotalHeaders  by Node_Name,Test_Id,_timeslice
| TotalHeaders/1024/1024 as  TotalHeaders 
| transpose row _timeslice column  Node_Name,Test_Id

$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary.Byte.Response.ContentType.Html","NodeName","TestId","TestDetail.Name"  as Html,Node_Name,Test_Id,Test_Name
| timeslice 1m
| where Test_Name matches /^{{TestName}}$/
| avg (Html) as Html  by Node_Name,Test_Id,_timeslice
| Html/1024/1024 as  Html 
| transpose row _timeslice column  Node_Name,Test_Id

$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary.Byte.Response.ContentType.Script","NodeName","TestId","TestDetail.Name" as Script,Node_Name,Test_Id,Test_Name
| timeslice 1m | where Test_Name matches /^{{TestName}}$/
| avg (Script) as Script  by Node_Name,Test_Id,_timeslice
| Script/1024/1024 as  Script
| transpose row _timeslice column Node_Name,Test_Id

$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary.Byte.Response.ContentType.Css","NodeName","TestDetail.Name" as Css,Node_Name,Test_Name
| where Test_Name matches /^{{TestName}}$/ 
| avg (Css) as Css_in_bytes  by Test_Name,Node_Name
| Css_in_bytes/1024/1024 as  Css_in_MB
| round (Css_in_MB, 2) as Css_in_MB
| sort by Css_in_MB
| fields  Test_Name, Node_Name, Css_in_MB
| limit 20

children.name: Catchpoint - Test Times
children.description: The Test Time dashboard focuses on displaying how much time was spent loading resources. It plots the metrics over time making it easier to identify trends.
children.title: Catchpoint - Test Times

queries.queryString:
$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary.Timing.DocumentComplete","NodeName","TestId","TestDetail.Name" as Document_Complete,Node_Name,Test_Id,Test_Name
| where Test_Name matches /^{{TestName}}$/| timeslice 1m | avg (Document_Complete) as Document_Complete  by Node_Name,Test_Id,_timeslice
| transpose row _timeslice column  Node_Name,Test_Id

$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary.Timing.Total","NodeName","TestId","TestDetail.Name" as Total,Node_Name,Test_Id,Test_Name
| where Test_Name matches /^{{TestName}}$/
| timeslice 1m
| avg (Total) as Total  by _timeslice, Node_Name,Test_Id
| transpose row _timeslice column  Node_Name,Test_Id

$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary.Timing.DomLoad","NodeName","TestDetail.Name","TestRuntime" as DomLoad,Node_Name,Test_Id,Test_Name
| where Test_Name matches /^{{TestName}}$/
| timeslice 1m |  avg (DomLoad) as DomLoad  by Node_Name,Test_Id,_timeslice
| transpose row _timeslice column Node_Name,Test_Id

queries.queryString:
$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary.Timing.ContentLoad","NodeName","TestId","TestDetail.Name" as ContentLoad,Node_Name,Test_Id,Test_Name
| where Test_Name matches /^{{TestName}}$/
| timeslice 1m
| avg (ContentLoad) as ContentLoad  by Node_Name,Test_Id,_timeslice
| transpose row _timeslice column  Node_Name,Test_Id

$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary.Timing.ContentType.Html","NodeName","TestDetail.Name" as Html,Node_Name,Test_Name
|  where Test_Name matches /^{{TestName}}$/
| avg (Html) as Response_Time  by Test_Name,Node_Name
| sort by Response_Time
| limit 20

$$logsrc 
| json field=_raw "Summary.Timing.ContentType.Css","NodeName","TestDetail.Name" as Css,Node_Name,Test_Name
|  where Test_Name matches /^{{TestName}}$/
| avg (Css) as Response_Time  by Test_Name,Node_Name
| sort by Response_Time
| limit 20
